1
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:40,640
Who lives in this house?

2
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,560
I checked, the owner is Yang Kaixin.

3
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,040
He's a professor at the conservatory.

4
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:45,280
Is the deceased him?

5
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:47,640
Can't be sure, the body's decomposed.

6
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:49,840
Decomposed? What do you mean?

7
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,640
We called a locksmith.

8
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,840
They opened the door.

9
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,000
You'll understand once you go in.

10
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,040
We can go in now.

11
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,519
Yes, the forensics team just left.

12
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,000
The medical examiner is still inside.

13
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,040
Captain Liu.

14
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,760
We're in trouble, boss.

15
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,919
I even wore a new pair of shoes.

16
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,520
I thought, since it's Xia Yu's birthday...

17
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,360
Then when it's your birthday,

18
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,159
let him buy you a new pair, problem solved.

19
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:16,719
Here.

20
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,840
Didn't you say not to wear it?

21
00:02:19,159 --> 00:02:21,680
It's for you to use in case you throw up.

22
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:23,360
You underestimate me, boss.

23
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:25,560
Brother Zhang.

24
00:02:25,759 --> 00:02:26,280
I'm here.

25
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,319
Morning.

26
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:32,120
Teacher Qin.

27
00:02:32,159 --> 00:02:33,479
What's this red stuff?

28
00:02:33,639 --> 00:02:34,759
Maggot shells.

29
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:37,719
Stick to the edge when you walk past.

30
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:55,840
Your forensics team

31
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,319
Why did you leave so quickly today?

32
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,439
We finished collecting everything.

33
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:01,199
Nothing useful was found.

34
00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:02,400
It's been too long.

35
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,159
Even if there was anything, it would have been destroyed by the body fluids.

36
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,159
How long has it been?

37
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:09,120
At least a few months.

38
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,039
Look how badly decomposed it is.

39
00:03:11,879 --> 00:03:13,719
This isn't just badly decomposed.

40
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:14,960
There's nothing left.

41
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,319
Exactly.

42
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,280
I'm worried too.

43
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,240
I'm thinking about how to transport the whole thing back.

44
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,919
Master, if Xia Yu were here,

45
00:03:23,919 --> 00:03:25,120
would he faint?

46
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:27,680
I wouldn't.

47
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,879
Master, I just finished my work.

48
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,439
I heard there was a case, so I rushed over.

49
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,360
Here, put on a mask. Don't throw up here.

50
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,360
I didn't bring one.

51
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:39,360
Is there a phone at the scene?

52
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,159
Haven't seen one.

53
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,439
Are there any clues on the body right now?

54
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,520
Clues?

55
00:03:45,639 --> 00:03:46,919
Judging by the physical features,

56
00:03:46,919 --> 00:03:49,280
it's a male. The rest depends on luck.

57
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:54,879
Can you two see clearly from that far away?

58
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:56,319
We can see clearly, sir.

59
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,199
Get closer.

60
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:00,840
Where are you now?

61
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:02,280
Hurry up.

62
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,840
I can't handle this by myself.

63
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,159
You'll know when you get here. Hurry up!

64
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,479
How did that thing end up there?

65
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:12,719
This cardboard box—

66
00:04:12,759 --> 00:04:14,680
When we first came in, it was at the door.

67
00:04:16,879 --> 00:04:18,560
Judging by the bloodstains on the wall,

68
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,279
and the position of the body,

69
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:22,240
it was probably a slash to the neck from behind.

70
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,639
Looks like it.

71
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,279
A neck slash from behind.

72
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,560
Could it be that the killer knew the victim?

73
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,720
There was no sign of defense.

74
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,720
You two—

75
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:41,279
Check inside the room.

76
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:44,720
Mr. Qin, can we go in?

77
00:04:44,759 --> 00:04:46,120
All evidence has been collected. You can go in.

78
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,920
You can enter the bedroom too.

79
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,680
Keep an eye out.

80
00:05:00,879 --> 00:05:01,680
Sir.

81
00:05:02,319 --> 00:05:04,519
Professor Yang sure has a high standard of living.

82
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,480
Even his mouthwash is imported.

83
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,240
What is this?

84
00:05:26,279 --> 00:05:27,079
Bianzhong

85
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:29,240
An ancient musical instrument

86
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,519
I just heard a police officer mention it

87
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:34,519
He said Professor Yang teaches this

88
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,480
He seems to be an authority on it

89
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,439
The most important thing right now

90
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:44,040
is to identify the deceased

91
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:45,360
Wearing only underwear

92
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:48,279
The deceased most likely lived here

93
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,079
You two go check around the area

94
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,160
See if Professor Yang himself lived here

95
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:53,959
If so

96
00:05:54,839 --> 00:05:56,480
Was he living alone or with others?

97
00:05:57,199 --> 00:05:58,319
If it was rented out

98
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,439
Ask who the tenants are

99
00:06:00,439 --> 00:06:01,160
Understood, okay

100
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:17,240
No one's here, right?

101
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:24,399
Let's go, let's head down first

102
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,319
Boss, we've confirmed from multiple sources

103
00:06:32,319 --> 00:06:32,879
The resident in 201

104
00:06:32,879 --> 00:06:34,680
Usually, only Professor Yang lives there

105
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:35,879
What about his family?

106
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,600
His family has four members

107
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,959
His wife, a son, and a daughter

108
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:40,319
His wife's name is Wu Minru

109
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,399
His son's name is Yang Mo

110
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:42,399
His daughter's name is Yang Wei

111
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:43,920
Why don't they live together?

112
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:45,519
We'd have to ask his family about that

113
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,240
It's just upstairs, 206

114
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:53,800
Should we go up?

115
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:00,079
Be careful

116
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,319
Coming, coming! Who is it?

117
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,720
Who are you looking for?

118
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,079
Are you Professor Yang Kaixin's...

119
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:24,120
I'm his wife.

120
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,319
You are...

121
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:28,519
We're from the Haiming City Criminal Police.

122
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:32,199
May I ask if Professor Yang usually lives at

123
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,160
Unit 201, Building 9, Huacui?

124
00:07:36,079 --> 00:07:37,199
Yes, that's right.

125
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:39,319
There was an incident there.

126
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,959
So we're here to ask you a few questions.

127
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,399
An incident?

128
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,000
What kind of incident?

129
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,800
How many people live here?

130
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,759
Just my son and me.

131
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,800
My daughter doesn't come back often.

132
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:54,160
Doesn't Professor Yang usually come back either?

133
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,399
Right, we have two apartments.

134
00:07:57,399 --> 00:07:58,560
He lives at the other one.

135
00:07:59,439 --> 00:08:01,199
Why don't you all live together?

136
00:08:02,639 --> 00:08:04,680
He has to supervise students, you know.

137
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:07,439
Students often come to see him.

138
00:08:07,439 --> 00:08:09,360
To discuss academic issues.

139
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,600
Or to work on performance techniques and such.

140
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:14,160
He needs a separate room.

141
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,000
So we let him have that place.

142
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,319
Although this is a one-bedroom apartment,

143
00:08:23,519 --> 00:08:25,360
it's actually quite spacious.

144
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:26,319
Usually,

145
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:28,920
my daughter is studying at university in Jiangning.

146
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:30,240
She doesn't come home very often.

147
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:32,519
So there's plenty of space.

148
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,600
Was that when your children were little?

149
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,399
Yes.

150
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,600
What are your children's names?

151
00:08:40,519 --> 00:08:42,679
My son's name is Yang Mo.

152
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,960
"Mo" as in "end."

153
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,679
My daughter's name is Yang Wei.

154
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:46,799
"Wei" as in "future."

155
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,919
Their father chose both names.

156
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:51,080
He said one doesn't compete to be first,

157
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,200
and the other is uncertain.

158
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,720
Please think carefully.

159
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,399
When was the last time you saw Professor Yang?

160
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,320
It's been almost half a year.

161
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:07,200
The last time was on his birthday.

162
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,759
He came back and we had a meal together.

163
00:09:08,919 --> 00:09:09,919
When was his birthday?

164
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,080
July 2nd.

165
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,519
We haven't seen each other since then.

166
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:14,320
No.

167
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:20,559
Why? Has he been reported?

168
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,159
Reported?

169
00:09:22,759 --> 00:09:23,960
Who would report him?

170
00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:25,840
No.

171
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,559
I'm just asking.

172
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,039
Nonsense.

173
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:37,519
Where does your son work? What time does he get off?

174
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,799
My son works in editing.

175
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:41,919
No, not at that magazine.

176
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,399
He does sales.

177
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:45,919
He sells ads.

178
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,879
He doesn't have a fixed time to get off work.

179
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,320
He's been on a business trip these past couple of days.

180
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,519
He hasn't come back yet.

181
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:56,200
What exactly is going on?

182
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,320
Here's the situation.

183
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,519
At Professor Yang's residence,

184
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,120
a homicide has occurred.

185
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:06,600
But the victim's identity

186
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,600
has not yet been confirmed.

187
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,600
Since your son and daughter aren't home,

188
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:12,960
we'll need you to come with us in person.

189
00:10:16,399 --> 00:10:17,200
A homicide?

190
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:40,320
I bought all of these for him.

191
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:46,200
Ms. Wu, please don't get upset, don't worry.

192
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:50,840
Ms. Wu, please calm down, let's talk this through.

193
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,720
Please, try to stay calm.

194
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:55,320
We

195
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,120
still need to confirm some things.

196
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,120
How about we call your son and daughter

197
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,879
and have them come keep you company?

198
00:11:06,759 --> 00:11:08,519
They're both quite busy.

199
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,720
I can handle this myself.

200
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,559
We need to ask you a few questions.

201
00:11:19,919 --> 00:11:21,480
From July until now,

202
00:11:22,159 --> 00:11:23,480
it's been such a long time.

203
00:11:23,799 --> 00:11:25,519
Haven't you been in touch with each other at all?

204
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:28,240
Old Yang,

205
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,120
he's good in every way,

206
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,919
except he doesn't like us bothering him.

207
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,159
We live close by, too.

208
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,519
If something comes up, he just comes home himself.

209
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:47,159
He doesn't let us call him, either.

210
00:11:49,559 --> 00:11:51,799
So how often does he come home?

211
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:57,080
It's hard to say.

212
00:11:58,919 --> 00:12:02,399
Sometimes he comes back quite often.

213
00:12:02,759 --> 00:12:04,519
If he's especially busy over there,

214
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:09,000
it's normal for him to come back only once every few months.

215
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:13,200
So with him gone for so long,

216
00:12:14,279 --> 00:12:15,960
hasn't the school contacted you?

217
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:20,200
No, they haven't.

218
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,720
How could the school not know either?

219
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,720
I've really seen something new today.

220
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,960
I've never seen anything this tragic.

221
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,480
It's been such a long time, you know.

222
00:12:35,759 --> 00:12:37,159
What can you even tell from the body now?

223
00:12:37,879 --> 00:12:39,399
I think we can first rule out

224
00:12:39,679 --> 00:12:40,720
robbery and murder.

225
00:12:41,519 --> 00:12:43,279
Not bad, you're making progress.

226
00:12:44,039 --> 00:12:46,120
You can even talk about the crime scene while eating.

227
00:12:46,799 --> 00:12:47,600
Go on.

228
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,679
You see, although there are signs of the scene being disturbed,

229
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:53,840
all the valuables, bankbooks,

230
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,200
and cards were untouched.

231
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:57,159
They killed someone,

232
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,519
made such a commotion,

233
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,559
and didn't take anything? That doesn't make sense.

234
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,080
So we can rule out robbery and murder.

235
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,120
Then the signs of disturbance at the scene

236
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,679
were most likely staged.

237
00:13:07,039 --> 00:13:08,919
The victim was in their underwear.

238
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,080
The person who killed him

239
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,320
must have been someone he knew well.

240
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,960
And precisely because it was someone familiar,

241
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,320
they needed to fake the scene to mislead us.

242
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:34,080
Xiaoli

243
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,759
Bring a case of cold beer.

244
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,799
Okay, boss.

245
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,919
Lei, Lei!

246
00:13:38,639 --> 00:13:40,000
What brings you here, Lei?

247
00:13:40,159 --> 00:13:41,080
Gangzi is here.

248
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,200
I had to come.

249
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:44,519
You even dared to take food to go last time.

250
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,120
You've gotten bold.

251
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,279
Lei, stop messing around.

252
00:13:48,279 --> 00:13:49,759
Come on, let's go.

253
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,080
Why did it go dark? Is there a power outage?

254
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:56,720
Happy birthday to you.

255
00:13:56,720 --> 00:14:00,240
Happy birthday to you.

256
00:14:00,559 --> 00:14:04,039
Happy birthday to you.

257
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:05,279
You even prepared this for me?

258
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:06,120
Go ahead, say it.

259
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,799
Make a wish.

260
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:09,799
Okay.

261
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,600
Okay.

262
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,320
Lei, I just went to the kitchen.

263
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,480
Why is your table gone?

264
00:14:25,759 --> 00:14:27,159
I threw it out.

265
00:14:28,279 --> 00:14:29,840
You must be making money now.

266
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,639
Zhang, what does your report mean?

267
00:15:02,159 --> 00:15:03,120
It means

268
00:15:03,279 --> 00:15:04,759
other than the identity being confirmed,

269
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:07,279
nothing else can be confirmed.

270
00:15:07,759 --> 00:15:09,320
Whether it was strangulation or stabbing,

271
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,320
there's no way to determine.

272
00:15:13,519 --> 00:15:14,559
Hello, may I ask something?

273
00:15:14,679 --> 00:15:15,120
Hello.

274
00:15:15,159 --> 00:15:16,240
Which apartment is moving out?

275
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:16,960
202.

276
00:15:17,279 --> 00:15:17,720
202.

277
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,480
That's right.

278
00:15:20,879 --> 00:15:21,480
Let's go.

279
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:24,440
I always thought that Old Yang

280
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,840
was bound to get into trouble.

281
00:15:26,279 --> 00:15:28,320
